org.rdkit.knime.util

Class InputDataInfo.EmptyCellException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • org.rdkit.knime.util.InputDataInfo.EmptyCellException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Enclosing class:
    InputDataInfo

    public static class InputDataInfo.EmptyCellException
extends java.lang.Exception
    This exception is thrown, when an empty cell was encountered during processing, which had an Empty Cell Policy DeliverEmptyValue or StopExecution assigned.
    Author:
    Manuel Schwarze
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors

      EmptyCellException(java.lang.String message, InputDataInfo inputDataInfo, RowKey rowKey)
      Creates a new empty cell policy exception, which states that an empty input cell was encountered with the specified empty cell policy, that lead to this exception.

      • stopsNodeExecution

        public boolean stopsNodeExecution()
        Determines, if the exception should lead to a full stop of processing or not.
        Returns:
        True, if execution should fully stop. False, if it is good enough to create a full set of empty result cells.
